HEADWORD: macarena
<hw>macarena</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a dance performed by dancers in a
line, or several lines, consisting mainly of hand and arm movements;
also, the name of the song to which the dance is usually performed. It
became popular in 1996.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

